title: For Sale/Trade:  Simplicity Regent 26hp Riding Mower
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Simplicity Riding Lawn Mower with a 38" deck. Parents owned it since new, it had one of Kohler's single cylinder engines in it (well known for issues, feel free to google search it). Long story short the engine blew and I bought it as a little project.

I put a brand new Kohler 26hp Twin Cylinder engine in it. I still haven't ran it long enough to change the original break in oil yet. As you can imagine the boost in power is very nice, especially for thicker grass. The engines both spin at the same RPM, so it doesn't put any additional stress on components, just offers more torque for higher demand. Motor swap was pretty much a direct swap, but did require modification of the exhaust system, plastic motor cover under the metal orange one, and some longer throttle cables. 

Turns out that with my fence it takes me 30 min to mow my yard either way, thus is the reason I'm looking to sell it.

title: For Sale:   Very fine condition WWII German Luger pistol in 9mm that is an early "K" date gun made in 1934.
location: Copenhagen, NY, New York, United States
postcontent: Very fine condition WWII German Luger pistol in 9mm that is an early "K" date gun made in 1934. This scarce piece is serial #4270 with all matching numbers. Built by Mauser and has the S/42 toggle marking and the early stick eagle waffenampt proof on the right side of the barrel extension. Pistol is NOT import marked and looks professionally restored of the finish. Action is crisp and functions fine. Metal finish is a deep blue that shows little use. Trigger, safety, takedown lever and mag release all show much "straw" color. Bore is good with average rifling and a little gray. Checkered wood grips have a good fit and no cracks or chips. Mag is correct early aluminum bottom type with a Luftwaffe eagle proofmark and nonmatching number. A seldom seen early "K" date Luger pistol as only about 10,000 were made in 1934 at the beginning of the rearming of the German military. This nice example will make a fine addition to a collection, a great display and a nice Father's Day gift.

title: For Sale:  Taurus PT24/7 OSS DS .45
postcontent:
The Taurus PT24/7,  if my memory serves me right, won the National Rifle Association (NRA) Handgun of the Year award in 2005. The OSS models feature a 5.25 inch match grade forged barrel  and a 3 position safety system - the bottom position enables the pistol to fire, the middle setting puts it in 'safe' condition, and the upper decocks the striker. This arrangement gives the user several carry options. The OSS retains the loaded chamber indicator of the other 24/7 models, and additionally allows visual verification that the pistol is ready to fire as the red end of the striker can be seen when the pistol is cocked.

This PT24/7 OSS DS is  chambered in .45 cal, has a 5.25 barrel, night sights, fixed rear sight, and under barrel rail.  It comes with original case and manual, two 12 round mags, cleaning brush, two keys for locking/unlocking firearm, and mag loading assist device.  I have several .45s and they don't need to sit unused so I'm weeding through the less often used ones. Maybe you can put it to better use than I have.
